  72. ‌  type info = {

  77. ‌  let info_of_raw (info : nativeint) =
  78.     let open Nativeint in
  79.     let arity =
  80.       (* signed: negative for tupled functions *)
  81.       if Sys.word_size = 64 then
  82.         to_int (shift_right info 56)
  83.       else
  84.         to_int (shift_right info 24)
  85.     in
  86. ‌    let start_env =
  87.       (* start_env is unsigned, but we know it can always fit an OCaml
  88.          integer so we use [to_int] instead of [unsigned_to_int]. *)
  89.       to_int (shift_right_logical (shift_left info 8) 9) in
  90.     { arity; start_env }

  92.   (* note: we expect a closure, not an infix pointer *)
  93. ‌  let info (obj : t) =
  94.     assert (tag obj = closure_tag);
  95.     info_of_raw (raw_field obj 1)
  96. end

  98. module Extension_constructor =
  99. struct
  100. ‌  type t = extension_constructor

  104.       if (is_block x) && (tag x) <> object_tag && (size x) >= 1 then field x 0
  105.       else x

  107. ‌    let name =

  110.     in

  114.   let [@inline always] name (slot : t) =
